# Coding Style (ECC-inspired)

## Immutability (pragmatic)

- Prefer **new values / new objects** over mutating shared state when the cost is low (DTOs, value objects, returned collections).
- **PHP / Eloquent**: mutating a loaded model for persistence is normal; still avoid surprising in-place mutation of arrays passed through many layers—prefer clear assignment or copies where it aids readability.

## File organization

- **Many small, focused files** beat few large ones: high cohesion, low coupling.
- Target roughly **200–400 lines** per file when practical; treat **~800 lines** as a signal to split.
- Organize by **feature/domain**, not only by technical type.

## Error handling

- Handle errors **explicitly** at boundaries (HTTP, queues, external APIs).
- **User-facing**: clear, safe messages; **server-side**: enough context to debug (without leaking secrets).

## Input validation

- Validate at **system boundaries** (HTTP Form Requests, console args, webhooks).
- Prefer **schema-style** validation (Laravel rules, typed DTOs) over ad hoc checks.
- **Never trust** external payloads (clients, third-party APIs, uploaded files).

## Quality checklist (before calling work done)

- [ ] Readable names; functions stay small (guide: under roughly **50 lines**).
- [ ] Avoid deep nesting (guide: at most roughly **4 levels**).
- [ ] No stray debug output (`dd`, `dump`, `console.log` in committed code).
- [ ] No hardcoded secrets; use env/config.
- [ ] Errors are handled, not swallowed.
